> Forget takeout: The path to sweet-and-savory dinner bliss is only 30 minutes away!

> In this recipe, pork, pepper, and onion are coated in a sumptuous sweet chili sauce,
> and peanuts are transformed into the perfect crunchy topping. Everything comes
> together over a bed of fluffy rice. The result? A symphony of flavors and textures
> so delicious, you might just lick the bowl.

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@yellow onion{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups
water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until
rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered
off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a #large pan{}, preferably
nonstick, over medium-high heat.
Add @peanuts{1/2%ounce}, 2 TBSP water, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring
often, until water has evaporated and
peanuts are coated and lightly toasted,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in same pan
over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper
and onion; season with salt and @pepper{}.
Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly
browned, ~{6-9%minutes}.

Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over
medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season with
salt and pepper. Using a #spatula{}, press
into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until
browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and
continue cooking until beef is cooked
through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in veggies, then add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until mixture is
thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and lime zest to
taste. Season with salt.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with
beef mixture, peanuts, and cilantro.
Serve with lime wedges on the side.